      "content": "but that's the thing, a regular telescope wouldn't pick it up if it's built into the star system itself. if you were going to monitor an entire planet's cognitive patterns, you wouldnt use a radio tower, you'd use something that looks like a natural part of the sky so no one questions it. like, if the stars themselves are actually nodes in a massive array, that would be the perfect way to hide a surveillance network in plain sight, wouldnt it?",
